oxc-project/oxc#16841.body:
Given the following four cases, only the first two are allowed.

However our rust AST looks like:
```
pub enum TSModuleReference<'a> {
    ExternalModuleReference( /* … */ ),
    IdentifierReference( /* … */ ),
    QualifiedName( /* … */ ),
    ThisExpression( /* … */ ),
}
```

I don't think it makes sense to permit `ThisExpression` since it is invalid

```
import x = foo;
// Allowed

import x2 = foo3.bar;
// allowed

import x3 = require("foo3");
// Allowed

import x3 = "foo2";
// TS1003: identifier expected

import x4 = this;
// TS1359: Identifier expected. 'this' is a reserved word that cannot be used here.
```

