oxc-project/oxc#16889.body:
[REPL](https://playground.oxc.rs/#) with all information.

---

### Details

```ts
function myFn(options = {}) {
	/*! Without this destructuring, it will behave correctly  */
  const { onMove } = options;
  const nestedFn = (e) => {
		/*! This should not be transformed to the optional chaining operator */
    onMove == null ? void 0 : onMove(position.value, e);
  };
	nestedFn()
}

myFn()
```

**Setup**

1. Set the target to `chrome64` (or any other target that doesn't support nullish coalescing operator)
2. Run the code through the minifier

**Expected**: No nullish coalescing operator in the output
**Actual**: Nullish coalescing operator is part of the end code due to an optimization

```ts
// OPTIMIZED CODE
function myFn(options = {}) {
	/*! Without this destructuring, it will behave correctly  */
	let { onMove } = options;
	((e) => {
		/*! This should not be transformed to the optional chaining operator */
		onMove?.(position.value, e);
	})();
}
myFn();
```

---

The same might happen for other optimizations that should not be applied for certain targets that do not support them.

Originally reported in https://github.com/vitejs/rolldown-vite/issues/556

