### What version of Oxlint are you using?

latest

### What happened?

Inline tags like `@link` breaks jsdoc parsing. For example, the following code:

```ts
  /**
   * Creates a {@link SearchableMap} from an `Iterable` of entries
   *
   * @param entries Entries to be inserted in the {@link SearchableMap}
   * @returns A new {@link SearchableMap} with the given entries
   */
  static from<T = any>(entries: Iterable<Entry<T>> | Entry<T>[]): SearchableMap<T> {
    const tree = new SearchableMap<T>();

    for (const [key, value] of entries) tree.set(key, value);

    return tree;
  }
```

<img width="666" height="265" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4893103d-e9f4-4305-b479-837c7cd4c8c5" />

