### What happened?

The `react/no-array-index-key` rule fails to detect when a key is a value processed from the array index (e.g., through template literals or arithmetic expressions).

Example

```tsx
import "./App.css";

export function App() {
  const array = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

  return (
    <ul>
      {/* 1. Template Literals - Not detected */}
      {array.map((n, index) => (
        <li key={`abc${index}`}>{n}</li>
      ))}

      {/* 2. Arithmetic Expressions - Not detected */}
      {array.map((n, index) => (
        <li key={1 + index}>{n}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

